body:
When compiling RTL from multiple sources it is normal to compile them into separate SystemVerilog libraries. Doing this means they cannot interfere with each other.  Also you can compile multiple different modules with the same name into different libraries.

SystemVerilog configurations are used to select which library to elaborate a module from. As described in the SV LRM 2017 (Chapter 33 "Configuring the contents of a design").

Libraries and configurations have been part of Verilog for over 20 years.  Larger and larger designs are using Verliator and the open hardware revolution means that we are often combining code from multiple sources.  So it now makes sense to think about this, and I'm just wondering whether there is a plan to do this?

The example code linked below successfully compiles on the 3 commercial simulators, 1 equivalence checker and 1 DFT tool I have tried.  Verilator is the only tool that I've tried that doesn't compile this code.

[lib_conf_example.tar.gz](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/7905577/lib_conf_example.tar.gz)

adder_a.sv and buffer_a.sv must be compiled into the `lib_rtl_a` library.

adder_b.sv and buffer_b.sv must be compiled into the `lib_rtl_b` library.

adder_sim_tb.sv must be compiled into the `lib_verif` library.

config.sv must be compiled into the `lib_config` library.

Elaborating `a_tb_config` from the `lib_config` library, then simulating it tests the A version of the design.  Whereas elaborating `b_tb_config` from the `lib_config` library, then simulating it tests the B version of the design, even though the same testbench module, `adder_sim_tb`, is used for both.

For reference, this is the contents of `config.sv`:
```
// config.sv

// Config for verifying the A variant of m_adder
config a_tb_config;
  design lib_verif.adder_sim_tb;   // Top level TB is compiled into lib_verif
  // For the adder instance in the TB, use a_adder_config compiled into the lib_config library
  instance adder_sim_tb.u_m_adder use lib_config.a_adder_config:config;
  default liblist work;               // There should be nothing compiled into the work library
endconfig

// Config for verifying the B variant of m_adder
config b_tb_config;
  design lib_verif.adder_sim_tb;
  instance adder_sim_tb.u_m_adder use lib_config.b_adder_config:config;
  default liblist work;
endconfig

// Config for using the A variant of m_adder
config a_adder_config;
  design lib_rtl_a.m_adder;       // Top level in this config is the adder compiled into the lib_rtl_a library
  default liblist lib_rtl_a;      // look in lib_rtl_a for all other modules instanced below the top level
endconfig

// Config for using the B variant of m_adder
config b_adder_config;
  design lib_rtl_b.m_adder;
  default liblist lib_rtl_b;
endconfig
```

